# scripts/.identifier-denylist.sha256
#
# One sha256 hex digest per line. Each digest is the hash of a normalized
# (lowercased, single-spaced) client/engagement identifier shingle that must
# NEVER appear in the public tree. lint_skills.py hashes every 1- and 2-word
# shingle of each linted file and fails the build on any match.
#
# Plaintext names are NEVER stored here — only their hashes. To add a name,
# either append its sha256 digest below, or (maintainer convenience) drop the
# plaintext into the gitignored scripts/.identifier-denylist.local, which the
# linter hashes on the fly.
#
#   printf '%s' "acme corp" | shasum -a 256   # -> paste the digest here
#
# This file ships empty by default; the linter prints a NOTE when no digests
# are loaded. Add digests as engagements require.
